<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

<prosody rate="1.0" pitch="-1st">
Before you now stands the Eclipse Gate.<break time="3s"/>

It is massive.<break time="2s"/> Impossibly tall.<break time="2s"/> Made of black obsidian stone covered in ancient glyphs that shimmer with faint crimson light.<break time="3s"/> Two towering pillars frame an archway through which you can see nothing but shadow.<break time="2.5s"/> Deep.<break time="1.5s"/> Absolute.<break time="1.5s"/> Magnetic.<break time="3s"/>

Above the gate, suspended in the starless sky, hangs the moon.<break time="3s"/> But it is not the moon you know.<break time="2s"/> It is caught mid-eclipse, half swallowed in Earth's shadow, glowing a deep, blood-red crimson.<break time="3.5s"/> The Red Moon.<break time="2s"/> The moon of purging.<break time="2s"/> The moon of rebirth.<break time="3.5s"/>

You can feel the pull of the gate.<break time="2s"/> A gentle, inexorable magnetism drawing you forward.<break time="2.5s"/> You smell the air here, it is cool and metallic, like stone after rain, mixed with the faint sweetness of night-blooming flowers you cannot name.<break time="3.5s"/>

As you approach the threshold, a figure emerges from the shadows beside the gate.<break time="3s"/>

It is the Wise Elder.<break time="3s"/>

She is ancient beyond years, draped in robes the color of twilight, woven with silver threads that catch the red moonlight.<break time="3s"/> Her eyes are deep and kind, holding lifetimes of knowing.<break time="2.5s"/> In her weathered hands, she holds a simple wooden staff crowned with a crescent moon carved from bone.<break time="3.5s"/>

She speaks, and her voice is the sound of wind through canyon stone.<break time="3s"/>

"Only those ready to release what no longer serves may pass through the Eclipse Gate.<break time="2.5s"/> Only those willing to burn away the old self may walk the Red Moon.<break time="2.5s"/> Are you ready?"<break time="4s"/>

And from somewhere deep within you, a quiet, steady voice answers.<break time="2s"/> Yes.<break time="3s"/>

The Elder nods slowly.<break time="2s"/> She reaches into her robes and withdraws a small clay cup filled with dark, shimmering liquid.<break time="2.5s"/> It smells of earth and smoke and something faintly sweet, like wild honey.<break time="3s"/>

"Drink this," she says.<break time="2s"/> "It will open your inner sight."<break time="3s"/>

You take the cup.<break time="2s"/> The clay is warm against your palms.<break time="2s"/> You bring it to your lips and drink.<break time="3s"/>

The liquid is cool and silky, tasting of night air and distant stars and forgotten dreams.<break time="3s"/> As it slides down your throat, warmth blooms in your chest, spreading outward like golden roots, threading through your entire body.<break time="4s"/>

Your vision sharpens.<break time="2s"/> Colors deepen.<break time="2s"/> The glyphs on the gate begin to glow brighter, pulsing in rhythm with your heartbeat.<break time="3.5s"/>

The Elder steps aside and gestures toward the archway.<break time="2.5s"/>

"Step through," she whispers.<break time="2s"/> "The Phoenix awaits you on the other side."<break time="4s"/>

[SFX: Rising harmonic shimmer, crystalline ascent, 5 seconds, building anticipation]

And so you step forward.<break time="3s"/>

Your foot crosses the threshold, and reality bends.<break time="3s"/>

For a moment, you are weightless, suspended in infinite darkness.<break time="3s"/> There is no sound.<break time="2s"/> No sensation.<break time="2s"/> Only presence.<break time="3s"/>

And then, light.<break time="3s"/>

You emerge on the other side, and your breath catches.<break time="3s"/>

You are standing on the surface of the Red Moon.<break time="4s"/>

The ground beneath your feet is crimson dust, soft as velvet, warm to the touch even through the soles of your shoes.<break time="3s"/> The sky above is a vast ocean of stars, so many and so bright they seem to hum with silent song.<break time="3.5s"/> And directly overhead, enormous and radiant, hangs the Earth, half-lit, blue and green and swirled with white, impossibly beautiful.<break time="4s"/>

All around you, the red landscape undulates in gentle hills and valleys carved by ancient forces you can only imagine.<break time="3s"/> The air here is thin and sweet, tasting faintly of ozone and copper.<break time="3s"/>

In the distance, perhaps a hundred paces ahead, you see a structure.<break time="3s"/>

A circle of tall, standing stones, each carved from the same crimson rock as the moon itself.<break time="2.5s"/> In the center of the circle burns a fire unlike any fire you have ever seen.<break time="3s"/>

It is not orange or yellow.<break time="2s"/> It is deep red, shot through with veins of gold and violet, and it does not consume.<break time="2.5s"/> It simply burns, steady and eternal, casting long shadows across the moon dust.<break time="4s"/>

And rising from the flames, wings spread wide, is the Phoenix.<break time="4s"/>

[SFX: Ethereal fire crackle, deep whoosh of wings, layered harmonics, 4 seconds]

The Phoenix is magnificent.<break time="3s"/>

Its feathers shimmer in every shade of fire, crimson, gold, amber, rose, violet, shifting and glowing as though lit from within.<break time="3.5s"/> Its eyes are twin suns, blazing with ancient intelligence and infinite compassion.<break time="3s"/> When it spreads its wings, you feel the warmth of the flames wash over you, not burning, but cleansing, stripping away fear, doubt, hesitation.<break time="4s"/>

The Phoenix looks at you.<break time="2.5s"/> And you understand without words what must happen here.<break time="3s"/>

This is the place of purging.<break time="2s"/> This is the ritual fire that burns away karmic patterns, old wounds, outdated stories, limiting beliefs, everything you have carried that no longer serves your highest becoming.<break time="4.5s"/>

The Phoenix lowers its great head and speaks directly into your mind, its voice a symphony of crackling flame and ringing crystal.<break time="3.5s"/>

"Step into the circle.<break time="2s"/> Step into the fire.<break time="2s"/> Surrender what you no longer need, and I will burn it to ash.<break time="2.5s"/> You will not be harmed.<break time="2s"/> You will be reborn."<break time="4s"/>

And so, with steady breath and open heart, you walk forward.<break time="3s"/>

You step between the standing stones.<break time="2s"/> The heat intensifies, but it does not hurt.<break time="2.5s"/> It feels like coming home after a lifetime of wandering.<break time="3s"/>

You step into the flames.<break time="4s"/>

And the fire rises around you, a column of red and gold light spiraling upward into the star-filled sky.<break time="4s"/>

You feel it begin.<break time="3s"/>

Old memories surface.<break time="2s"/> Moments of shame.<break time="2s"/> Moments of failure.<break time="2s"/> Voices that told you that you were not enough.<break time="2.5s"/> Patterns inherited from generations past, fears that were never yours to carry.<break time="3.5s"/>

One by one, they rise.<break time="2s"/> And one by one, the Phoenix fire consumes them.<break time="3s"/>

You feel them dissolve.<break time="2s"/> Ash on the wind.<break time="2s"/> Gone.<break time="3s"/>

And in their place, something new begins to grow.<break time="3s"/>

From deep within your chest, a light begins to glow.<break time="3s"/> Small at first, no larger than a seed.<break time="2s"/> But with each breath, it grows brighter.<break time="2.5s"/> Warmer.<break time="2s"/> Stronger.<break time="3s"/>

This is your Inner Light.<break time="3s"/>

The truth of who you have always been beneath the layers of conditioning and fear.<break time="3s"/> The part of you that is infinite, eternal, unbreakable.<break time="3.5s"/>

The Phoenix fans its wings, and the flames surge higher, brighter, hotter, but still, you are not burned.<break time="3.5s"/> You are being refined.<break time="2s"/> Purified.<break time="2s"/> Remade.<break time="4s"/>

And then, in a sudden rush of wind and fire, the flames collapse inward, drawn into the light in your chest, and the Phoenix itself dissolves into a thousand glowing embers that swirl around you like a galaxy of fireflies.<break time="4.5s"/>

They spiral closer, closer, and then they pour into you, merging with your Inner Light, until you are blazing, radiant, a being of pure luminous energy standing on the surface of the Red Moon.<break time="5s"/>

[SFX: Crystalline chime cascade, ascending tones, shimmering, 4 seconds, triumphant]

You look down at your hands, and they glow softly from within, as though your very cells have been lit with starfire.<break time="3s"/> You feel lighter.<break time="2s"/> Freer.<break time="2s"/> More yourself than you have ever been.<break time="3.5s"/>

The standing stones begin to hum, a low, resonant tone that vibrates through the ground and up into your bones.<break time="3s"/> And from the ashes at your feet, something stirs.<break time="3s"/>

A small, perfect egg made of polished obsidian rises, floating into your outstretched hands.<break time="3s"/> It is warm, pulsing gently with its own heartbeat.<break time="3s"/>

You understand.<break time="2s"/> This is the seed of your new self.<break time="2s"/> This is what you will carry back.<break time="3s"/>

Behind you, the Eclipse Gate shimmers back into view, though you did not see it appear.<break time="2.5s"/> The Wise Elder stands beside it once more, smiling softly, her eyes gleaming with quiet pride.<break time="3.5s"/>

"You have done well," she says.<break time="2s"/> "The eclipse wanes.<break time="1.5s"/> It is time to return.<break time="2s"/> But you will not return as you were.<break time="2.5s"/> You carry the fire now.<break time="2s"/> You carry the light."<break time="4s"/>

You bow your head in gratitude to the Phoenix, to the Red Moon, to the fire that did not consume you but transformed you.<break time="4s"/>

And then you turn, cradling the obsidian egg against your heart, and you step back through the Eclipse Gate.<break time="4s"/>
</prosody>

[SFX: Soft descending tone, gentle return, 3 seconds, grounding]

